Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of seven (7) years.   Four (4) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Court finds the defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program after two (2) years of initial confinement, but defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2) Submit random urine screens and pay for same; 
3) AODA assessment and follow through; 
4) Full-time employment if able; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Cash bail applied.  
Minutes.
